layout: default
title: Design_and_simulation_of_a_FANUC_LR_mate_series_robotic_arm
---
##Designed and Simulated 6-DOF Robotic Arm: Modeled a complete FANUC LR Mate series robotic arm using SolidWorks 2022, focusing on mechanical design precision, realistic joint constraints, and industrial-level specifications.

- Performed Kinematic Analysis: Conducted forward and inverse kinematics calculations to analyze joint-space to task-space transformation, ensuring accurate reach, positioning, and orientation for complex movements.

- Dynamic Simulation and Control: Used MATLAB Simulink to simulate arm dynamics and test various control strategies, including PID and feedback loops, for improved stability, accuracy, and responsiveness.

- Validated Against Industrial Standards: Evaluated reach, payload, repeatability, and cycle time across multiple operational scenarios to align with FANUC’s real-world performance benchmarks.

- Optimized Trajectories and Motion Profiles: Implemented motion planning techniques to reduce cycle time and increase precision through trajectory optimization and smooth path interpolation.

- Integrated Feedback Control Systems: Simulated sensor-based feedback mechanisms to improve adaptive performance in variable environments, enhancing real-time control accuracy.

- Bridged Design and Simulation: Demonstrated strong integration between CAD modeling and control theory, providing critical insights into the interplay between mechanical design and robotics algorithms.

- Contributed to Robotics Engineering: Applied theoretical robotics principles in a practical simulation environment, reinforcing system-level thinking and engineering problem-solving for real-world automation challenges.
